url: >-
  https://multiagent-ai-lab.github.io/Antigravity-Nano-Research-Multiagentic-Core/
abstract: >-
  Antigravity Nano Research Multiagentic Core is an open-source educational
  and research framework that integrates multi-agent AI systems with
  computational nanotechnology. It provides a structured six-unit curriculum
  (25 Jupyter notebooks) covering nanoscale simulation, machine learning for
  materials, and multi-agent orchestration using LangGraph, CrewAI, Google ADK,
  and smolagents. The framework features a reproducible demonstration
  system (Au13 nanoclusters) executable without API keys, a unified LLM routing
  layer supporting four backends (OpenRouter, Google Gemini, OpenAI, Ollama),
  Graph RAG with four storage backends, and MCP (Model Context Protocol)
  integration for computational tools.
  All components are validated with 102 automated tests (pytest 9.0.2).
keywords:
  - multi-agent systems
  - nanotechnology
  - computational materials science
  - large language models
  - graph retrieval-augmented generation
  - model context protocol
  - scientific computing
  - educational framework
  - LangGraph
  - Python
